      <section>
        <title>Gold Standard ends implication</title>
        <chapter>
 	        <paragraph>
            In 1971, Nixon ended the gold standard, abolishing the
           convertibility of the dollar into gold and effectively
           decreeing the death of the gold standard and the birth of
           the floating system created by the USA.</paragraph>
          <paragraph>
            Since the dollar was detached from the gold, it has
           increased in value, while the gold reserves of the USA,
           which accounted for 70% of total world reserves, went
           down to 64%.</paragraph>
        </chapter>
